---
title: Chimichurri Pork Tenderloin with Honey-Roasted Carrots & Lime Rice
description: Chimichurri is the perfect condiment: it’s bright, tangy, herbaceous, and so versatile. Cilantro, garlic, lime, and cumin provide punchy flavors that lift everything they touch to new delicious heights. This week, the magical sauce is drizzled over pork tenderloin. On the side, we’re serving honey-roasted carrots and fluffy, lime-scented rice. The flavors are so harmonious, once you take a bite, you may find it impossible to put your fork down.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/5e5026b99e16cc20fb4c09c8-e737101b.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/chimichurri-pork-tenderloin-5e5026b99e16cc20fb4c09c8-5a15b90e.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/chimichurri-pork-tenderloin-5e5026b99e16cc20fb4c09c8
time required: 40 minutes
nutrition:
  calories: 770 kcal
  fat: 36 g
  saturated fat: 9 g
  carbohydrates: 66 g
  sugar: 17 g
  protein: 36 g
  fiber: 6 g
  sodium: 290 mg
cuisine: North America
course: main course
servings: 2
author: Michelle Doll Olson
---

Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat #oven{} to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all produce. Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{12%ounce} on a diagonal into 1-inch-thick pieces. Zest and quarter @lime{1} (for 4, zest 1 lime and quarter both). Mince or grate @garlic{2%clove}. Finely chop @cilantro{1/4%ounce}.

In a #small pot{}, combine @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}, ¾ cup water (1 1/2 cups for 4 servings), and a big pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, toss carrots on one side of a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%tsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack for ~{15%minutes} (you'll add the pork then). (For 4 servings, spread carrots out across entire sheet; roast on top rack until tender, 25-30 minutes total.)

Meanwhile, pat @pork tenderloin{12%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}. Season with @salt{}, @pepper{}, and half the @cumin{1%teaspoon} (you'll use the rest later). Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium heat. Add pork; sear, turning occasionally, until browned all over, ~{4-8%minutes}. Once carrots have roasted 15 minutes, remove sheet from oven; add pork to empty side. Continue roasting until pork is cooked through and carrots are tender, ~{10-12%minutes} more. (For 4 servings, add pork to a second sheet; roast on middle rack.)

In a #small bowl{}, combine cilantro, a pinch of @garlic{}, remaining cumin, @olive oil{2%TBSP} (3 TBSP for 4 servings), and a big squeeze of lime juice. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Add more lime juice or garlic if you feel like something's missing. Add a @?chili flakes{1%tsp} if desired.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in lime zest, @butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4 servings), @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Thinly slice pork crosswise. Toss roasted carrots with @honey{2%tsp} and a pinch of chili flakes to taste. Divide rice, pork, and carrots between plates. Drizzle pork with chimichurri. Serve with any remaining lime wedges on the side.